(151, 'com.groveair.spectator', 'SEC Football Guide 2013', 'Rogers D. Stephens', '***** UPDATED FOR 2013 SEASON *****<p>Key information at your fingertips while watching SEC college football games. Use this app to view rosters of both teams, schedules, rankings, scores of other games, etc.<p>No cell service in the stadium? No problem. Team rosters and schedules are loaded to your device so they will be accessible when cellular/internet coverage is unavailable in the stadium!<p>Awarded InformationWeek Top 20 App (2010)<p>Features:<p>* While watching a game, from 1 screen easily view rosters for both teams, schedules, and scores of other games<p>* Sort / filter rosters 5 ways - by jersey, name, position, year, and state where the player is from<p>* Roster and Schedule for all 14 SEC teams AND non-conference opponents<p>* Easy access to News for your favorite team.  Customize alerts when news is published.<p>* Convenient web links to Scores and Nat&#39;l Ranking<p>View the YouTube video for a demo (prior year&#39;s app but functionality is similar).<p>Alabama Crimson Tide, Arkansas Razorbacks, Auburn Tigers, Florida Gators, Georgia Bulldogs, Kentucky Wildcats, LSU Tigers, Mississippi State Dawgs, Ole Miss Rebels, South Carolina Gamecocks, Tennessee Volunteers, Vanderbilt Commodores, Missouri Tigers, Texas A&amp;M Aggies (and ALL non-conference opponents)', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.groveair.spectator', 'http://lh3.ggpht.com/krX1w9hixHg61KVI7N90g6JDCBKZuyWjlOY1G2OaDdzNfRtVfdDKvG-NgR1daUHFjZw', 4.12, 'SPORTS', '$1.99', '1,000+', 'android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION'),
(152, 'com.Samuel_Bryant.Ole_Miss_Circuit', 'Ole Miss Circuit', 'Samuel Bryant', 'This app is specifically designed to show University of Mississippi (Ole Miss) students about how long it will take to walk from one campus building to another based on walking speed (2.7, 3.1, 3.5, or 3.75 mph). Most colleges allow only 10 minutes between courses and sometimes it takes longer than that to get to the next class.<p>There are two ways to look up the time it will take to get from one building to the other. There is a map you can use to select the buildings. There is also a list of buildings you can choose from.<p>Your position is shown on the map along with all of the campus buildings. Tapping on a building will bring up a list of other buildings to choose from indicating your destination. It will display four walking speeds and the time (in minutes) it will take to walk to the chosen building from the selected list.', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.Samuel_Bryant.Ole_Miss_Circuit', 'http://lh5.ggpht.com/f9vVX7TvuvAaCvh6C6_B2NB-KNW_LCLlk2Kduct6GY-3FzLUzLxlvgZmHjmhVKKH6Q', 0.00, 'BOOKS_AND_REFERENCE', '$0.99', '10+', 'android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION, android.permission.ACCESS_LOCATION_EXTRA_COMMANDS, android.permission.CAMERA, android.permission.GET_ACCOUNTS, android.permission.MODIFY_AUDIO_SETTINGS, android.permission.READ_CONTACTS, android.permission.RECORD_AUDIO, android.permission.RECORD_VIDEO, android.permission.WRITE_CONTACTS, android.permission.READ_CALL_LOG, android.permission.WRITE_CALL_LOG'),
(153, 'com.vsporto.rebel', 'Rebel Sports Radio', 'VSporto', 'Rebel Sports Radio gives die-hard Ole Miss fans exactly what they want:  All Rebels. All the time. Tune in for the latest news, opinion and analysis of Ole Miss athletics 24 hours a day. We’ve brought every expert, beat writer and pundit together to make sure you’re up to speed on every aspect of Rebel Sports.  Check out a few of our shows below:<p>-	The Ole Miss Beat with Parrish Alford<br>-	The Flagship with Ben Garrett and Steven Godfrey<br>-	Recruiting Central with Christian Byrd<br>-	The Show Up North with Will East and Tyler Bischoff<br>-	Jake&#39;s Take with Jake Adams and Ken Edwards<p>Listen in to the live stream to see what’s happening NOW or check out our OnDemand section in case you missed a show or two.  You can also tune on our homepage at RebelSportsRadio.com. <p>With Rebel Sports Radio, you can take your fandom to the next level. Hotty Toddy!', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.vsporto.rebel', 'http://lh5.ggpht.com/40TOei6JzdULutF_dd5t51MfTbEdlN1-0DcWUxnO8aBX7MAGOhXeeTqeA-c_DMiNBL6s', 4.32, 'SPORTS', 'Free', '1,000+', 'android.permission.ACCESS_MOCK_LOCATION, android.permission.BROADCAST_STICKY'),
(154, 'com.mobilerush.olemissbasketballrush', 'Ole Miss Basketball *FREE*', 'Mobile Rush LLC.', 'Do you love Ole Miss Rebels Basketball? The Ole Miss Basketball Rush is now available to you for FREE but for a *Limited Time*! Now you can catch the Ole Miss Rebels Basketball game!<p>Features of this app include:<p>* Ole Miss Rebels Men&#39;s Basketball News<br>* Ole Miss Rebels Men&#39;s Basketball Videos<br>* Ole Miss Rebels Men&#39;s Basketball Photos<br>* Fan Wall<br>* Ole Miss Rebels Men&#39;s Basketball Shop<br>* Talk Trash Against Other Fans<br>* Connect Easily With Mobile Rush<br>* NCAA Men&#39;s Basketball Scores<br>* NCAA Men&#39;s Basketball Standings<br>* Ole Miss Rebels Men&#39;s Basketball Schedule<br>* Ole Miss Rebels Men&#39;s Basketball Roster<br>* and MORE!<p>DISCLAIMER: Mobile Rush is not affiliated with Ole Miss Rebels Basketball. But a 3rd party company that&#39;s dedicated to connecting Ole Miss Rebels Basketball fans with their team as best as possible. With wallpaper, live wallpapers, background and theme. 77777<p>The history of Ole Miss Rebels Basketball from Wikipedia.<p>The Mississippi Rebels men&#39;s basketball team represents the University of Mississippi in intercollegiate men&#39;s basketball. They have participated in the National Invitation Tournament in 1980, 1982, 1983, 1987, 1989, 2000, 2007, 2008, 2010, 2011 and 2012. In 2008 and 2010, they made it to the National Invitation Tournament Semifinals at Madison Square Garden. The Rebels have won the SEC Western Division in 1997, 1998, 2001, 2007, and 2010. From 1999-2006, Rod Barnes coached the Rebels basketball team, and compiled a record of 141-109 during his tenure.<p>In 2007, Ole Miss hired Andy Kennedy, and the Rebs tied for first place in the SEC West during the 2006–2007 season. Led by the senior trio of Clarence Sanders, Bam Doyne, and Todd Abernethy, the Ole Miss men finished the year with a 21-13 record, including a 16-1 record at home inside Tad Smith Coliseum. They advanced to the second round of the National Invitation Tournament, before falling at Clemson University. In his debut season with the Rebels, Kennedy was named the 2007 SEC Coach of the Year by the Associated Press after guiding Ole Miss, a preseason last-place pick in the SEC West, to its first division title and most wins since 2001.<p>In the 2012-2013 season Ole Miss won just their second SEC Tournament title ever, and made the NCAA Tournament for the first time since 2002. Ole Miss also set a team record for most SEC wins in a season.', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.mobilerush.olemissbasketballrush', 'https://lh3.ggpht.com/eYbtsUSZukqkv_c8e_cdg43zn4wc_M4SG6I36havCSY0x6NUYUhWNOrqv51rv2rsHA', 0.00, 'SPORTS', 'Free', '1+', 'android.permission.GET_ACCOUNTS, com.mobilerush.olemissbasketballrush.permission.C2D_MESSAGE, com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEIVE'),
(155, 'com.eis', 'Rebel Rewards', 'Ole Miss', 'Do you love Ole Miss Sports and want to earn prizes for attending?  Ole Miss Athletics has teamed up with C Spire Wireless to offer the premier fan appreciation rewards program.  Download Rebel Rewards today, and start being rewarded for what you love doing the most, attending Ole Miss athletic events!<br> Application Features:<br>Up-to-date schedule of all Rebel Rewards events<br>Up-to-date leaderboards and prize tiers<br>Push notifications of all Rebel Rewards activities<br>Personalized dashboard for each user<br>Personalized I.D. number and barcode for each user', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.eis', 'http://lh5.ggpht.com/UNSo_cIq3qyMSXWdHB2O-4Xy6ul8bL-97g_igrIcVF5wMYpu58biajKeNkpQ11e9y10', 2.42, 'SPORTS', 'Free', '500+', ''),
