(656, 'com.rn.soundshare', 'rShare for Google Play Music', 'Rn Software', 'Share your Google Play Music activity on Facebook, Google+, or Twitter! rShare keeps track of your Google Play Music history and allows you to post the songs you&#39;ve listened to on Facebook, Google+, or Twitter. Each post is formatted and contains the artist, album, track, and album artwork. You can even post directly from your notification bar!<p>Requirements:<p>- A Facebook, Google+, or Twitter account.<br>- The Google Play Music app.<p>Usage Instructions:<p>- Play a song using Google&#39;s Play Music app.<br>- Start rShare.<br>- Tap on the share button next to the track name to post it.', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.rn.soundshare', 'https://lh3.ggpht.com/l0OQgDs9eJuZNJri8ZCfsDP8LYV9wHqe4tQm7whDGssyYtQpBL4nz8CFPZM2bbVV2yM', 4.56, 'MUSIC_AND_AUDIO', 'Free', '10,000+', 'com.android.vending.BILLING'),
(657, 'org.dyndns.jkiddo.gias', 'iTunes Google Music Share', 'jkiddo', 'Your music on the phone + this app = streaming from iTunes with no extra software<p><br> - iTunes Google Music Share is the perfect app when you want to share your music where YOU are. When your phone is connected to a wifi network, you will, by starting the app, be able to share all your music files located on your Google Music account directly onto the network into iTunes, also called a DAAP share.<p>IF YOU USE GOOGLE&#39;S 2-STEP VERIFICATION: Please create a application specific password (see <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/185833?hl%3Den&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNE64BpaAqpyIjLcBdC_0f7vJrIVAw" target="_blank">https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/185833?hl=en</a>) and use this for logging in.<p>Just start the app on your phone and open iTunes on your computer and your phone will be listed as an external library in iTunes, ready to be stream from. No extra software is needed to be installed on either your PC or Mac, just iTunes.<p><br>This app aims to provide some of the same functionality as the mt-daapd / Firefly Media Server / forked-daapd projects also do - merged with Google music.<p><br>In case of malfunction/you can&#39;t get it to work, try disabling your firewalls momentarily to see if that could be the cause.<p><br> - Happy streamin&#39;<p>As a sidenote - upon request pr. mail, I&#39;ll send you a PC version of the program if you like', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=org.dyndns.jkiddo.gias', 'https://lh5.ggpht.com/WLrvgT-urHLV0jGwdu-YBHcvrrFpJiAtxdlfMwdZ8gowJJHz30lb5YmwQhRPtYumdsJv', 3.90, 'MUSIC_AND_AUDIO', 'Free', '10,000+', 'android.permission.CHANGE_WIFI_MULTICAST_STATE, android.permission.UPDATE_DEVICE_STATS, android.permission.CHANGE_WIFI_STATE'),
(658, 'com.h6ah4i.android.music_visualizer2', 'Music Visualizer', 'h6a_h4i', '&quot;Music Visualizer&quot; plays music and renders beautiful visualized effects.<br>With &quot;Snoop mode or Live Wallpaper,&quot; this app provides visualization for another media player.<p><br>Announcements<br>--------------------------<p>* NOW BETA TESTING Ver.1.6.0<p>=================<br>Ver.1.6.0 beta<p>[New features]<br> - Added homescreen widget<br> - Support system default equalizer<br>[Improvements]<br> - Support &#39;Immersive mode&#39; full screen (requires Android 4.4)<br> - Bug fixes<br>=================<p>--------------------------<p>I made Music Visualizer app community on Google+. If you want to try a latest version app, please join the community and register as a app tester.<p>Step 1. Join to Music Visualizer  Google+ community<br><a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://plus.google.com/u/0/communities/108627545245152701806&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNErkjRkHQU4nihvYZSS4_xheMepDg" target="_blank">https://plus.google.com/u/0/communities/108627545245152701806</a><p>Step 2. Enable beta testing<br>https://play.google.com/apps/testing/com.h6ah4i.android.music_visualizer2<p>--------------------------<p>(*1) Limitations on Nexus 4, 5 and 7 (2013)<br><a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://plus.google.com/110898804228810455198/posts/6chmkb9ix1s&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNETSn-cmVaZn_YooLxrFdBY8U7zIg" target="_blank">https://plus.google.com/110898804228810455198/posts/6chmkb9ix1s</a><p>(*2) Limitations on Galaxy S4 (Snapdragon Quad core model)<br><a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://plus.google.com/110898804228810455198/posts/jXGKDLt9iTz&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNEGt-fEoAin098LmIC9aF0__PVOkA" target="_blank">https://plus.google.com/110898804228810455198/posts/jXGKDLt9iTz</a><p>Limitations on recent Motorola&#39;s phones (Moto X, DROID Mini, ...)<br><a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://plus.google.com/110898804228810455198/posts/QgqfNnwcD6Y&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNG7dwDrg-n3TejEvxk2rL5aQbVH3Q" target="_blank">https://plus.google.com/110898804228810455198/posts/QgqfNnwcD6Y</a><p>--------------------------<p><br>* Features<br> - 10 types of renderers and randomized of them<br>    (Waveform / Shiny Particles / Noise Flow / Colorful Orb / Simple Bars / Heart Beats / Laser / Digital Equalizer / Hex Tiles / Energy Sphere)<br> - Playback media in your phone<br> - Control by gestures<br> - Live wallpaper mode<br> - Daydream mode (for Android 4.2 or later only)<br> - Snoop mode (You can use this app with your another favorite media player!)<br> - External player app control<br> - Equalizer and audio effects<br> - Microphone input mode<p>* Gesture information<br> Single tap: Toggle media informations<br> Double tap: Play/Pause<br> Long press: Choose renderer<br> Swipe left: Previous<br> Swipe right: Next<br> Swipe up: Show media controls<br> Swipe down: Hide media controls<br> Circle (once): Repeat all track<br> Circle (twice): Repeat single track<br> &quot;S&quot; shape: Toggle shuffle<p> (for 2.3 Gingerbread only) <br> Touch screen edge of top-right: Show playing queue<p>* Notes<br> - If alternative wallpaper image picker not worked properly, please install QuickPic app.<br>   (QuickPic: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.alensw.PicFolder)<p>* Misc.<br> - This software uses third party components;<br>    + ViewPagerIndicator (<a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://viewpagerindicator.com/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNFq2DUz0nkQ-E6ImHqodsG7IjbeRg" target="_blank">http://viewpagerindicator.com/</a>)<br>    + android-ColorPickerPreference (<a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://github.com/attenzione/android-ColorPickerPreference/&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNEcLG3-xXy6ZBqUOl1RQ0RkZGMWfQ" target="_blank">https://github.com/attenzione/android-ColorPickerPreference/</a>)<br>    + MultiSelectListPreferenceCompat (<a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://github.com/h6ah4i/mulsellistprefcompat&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNEm8dLdurGGxWSy_Q09KfsBJ6fQvA" target="_blank">https://github.com/h6ah4i/mulsellistprefcompat</a>)<br>    + Poweramp API Lib (<a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://github.com/maxmpz/powerampapi&amp;sa=D&amp;usg=AFQjCNGNSJiN9gt9wGEWgSVlNFny3mEHBw" target="_blank">https://github.com/maxmpz/powerampapi</a>)<br> - Russian support (Thx. ????? ???????)<p> Now I&#39;m testing on 10 devices / GPUs. <br>  - Google Nexus 10 (Dual Core 1.7 GHz + Mali T604)<br> - Google Nexus 7 2013 (Quad Core 1.51 GHz + Adreno 320) (*1)<br> - Google Nexus 7 2012 (Quad Core 1.2 GHz + Tegra 3 T30L) (*1)<br> - Google Nexus 5 (Quad Core 2.28 GHz + Adreno 330) (*1)<br> - Samsung Galaxy S4 SC-04E (Dual Core 1.9 GHz + Adreno 320) (*2)<br> - Samsung Galaxy S II SC-02C (Dual Core 1.2 GHz + Mali-400 MP)<br> - MOTOROLA PHOTON (Dual Core 1.2 GHz + Tegra 250)<br> - HTC EVO 3D (Dual Core 1.2 GHz + Adreno 220)<br> - SHARP INFOBAR A01 (Single Core 1.4 GHz + Adreno 205)<br> - Panasonic P-07C (Single Core 1.0 GHz + PowerVR SGX530) (* Mic input mode doesn&#39;t work)<p>* In future release...<br> - New renderers<br> - Usage manual &amp; tutorial<p>* Recommended device specs.<br> CPU: Dual core or above<br> GPU: Mali-400MP, Tegra 2, PowerVR SGX540, Adreno 220 or avobe', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.h6ah4i.android.music_visualizer2', 'http://lh5.ggpht.com/6y9INSWqkf7IpfvkfEeczBkmJYp_lz6NDdNvo1CeKG6wdeBrVb1OBQ44jJO5sltUTRw', 4.48, 'MUSIC_AND_AUDIO', 'Free', '100,000+', 'android.permission.RECORD_AUDIO, android.permission.MODIFY_AUDIO_SETTINGS, android.permission.BLUETOOTH'),
(659, 'net.kepano.automusic', 'Auto Play Google Music', 'kepano', 'This application will auto play Google&#39;s &quot;Play Music&quot; when a headphone is inserted into the headphone jack.  This program will also allow the auto play to work with Bluetooth devices.  This does not guarantee the music will be playing through the Bluetooth headset.<p> -Any time a headphone is plugged into the auxiliary jack &quot;Play Music&quot; will start playing.<br> -Has the option to start phone starts or is rebooted<br>      -This will prevent you have having to enable the application manually.<p>  Permissions<br>  -Network Communication <br>      -This is ONLY for bluetooth option.  I do not and will not ever have annyoing ads.  I hate that it is called a Network Communication because people believe it hits the internet.<br>       -Again this is only to be able to read and dectect the bluetooth devices<p><br> -Future Releases:<br>      *Give the ability to set it to not turn on when certain Apps are actively open (ex when FM Radio app is open and headphones are plugged in we don&#39;t want to start playing our music).<p> -Known Issues:<br>      (Possible Fix in 1.2.2) *Sometimes does not detect initial headphone plug-in but will detect subsequent plug-ins', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=net.kepano.automusic', 'http://lh4.ggpht.com/BNzPPjbcmO5tYJFPOZRzmlLD6gDyL-vex_vLUZYqIANDCpOT047odIeg4vZJ8fJfgQo', 4.34, 'MUSIC_AND_AUDIO', 'Free', '10,000+', 'android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED, android.permission.BLUETOOTH'),
(660, 'net.tsunamisoft.fanmusic', 'The Beat: Music Videos by Fans', 'TsunamiSoft', '?? DISCLAIMER: This app does NOT contain any official musicvideos or audio recordings, it simply showcases the best fan-made music. All linked videos are publicly available on Google&#39;s own video services; we do not host any videos ourselves. The makers of this mobile video player app are not associated with the artists or franchises mentioned below. If you would like your video removed, please contact us. ??<p>The Beat: Music Videos by Fans presents the greatest, hottest and most incredible fan-made music videos, featuring hundreds of songs inspired by popular artists, TV shows, movies, video games, and anime! New videos are added frequently -- contact us if you have a suggestion!<p><br>Songs inspired by fans&#39; favorite musicians, including:<p>***List removed due to Google Play&#39;s search policy***<br>There are hundreds of categories including most popular (and some unpopular) artists, but it now seems that we may not be allowed to list them in the description. We will request clarification from Google.<p><br>Music videos inspired by films and TV shows, including:<p>***List removed due to Google Play&#39;s search policy***<p><br>Music inspired by video games, including:<p>***List removed due to Google Play&#39;s search policy***<p><br>Music videos inspired by Japanese anime, including:<p>***List removed due to Google Play&#39;s search policy***<p>And more!', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=net.tsunamisoft.fanmusic', 'http://lh6.ggpht.com/XM9ptA_-flPoPEimYPHEgsSphCtGyUi-z5fdjKvSiID_m77yKgPek_Ea73uLr8EYY9eu', 4.18, 'ENTERTAINMENT', 'Free', '100,000+', ''),
(661, 'br.com.rodrigokolb.musicequalizer', 'Music Equalizer', 'Rodrigo Kolb', 'Music Equalizer - The best EQ sound for your Android<br>Let their songs much better with the Music Equalizer!<br>Improve your phone or tablet&#39;s sound quality now!<p>Features:<br>* 5 Band EQ controller<br>* Bass Booster<br>* Virtualizer mode for best headphone results<br>* 10 Presets<br>* Save custom presets<br>* 4x1 widget<br>* Notification shortcut available for quick access<br>* Works with all screen resolutions - Cell Phones and Tablets (HD)<br>* Free<p>Music Equalizer works with the most players, like:<br>* Android™ Music Player<br>* Winamp<br>* Google Music<br>* MixZing<br>* Poweramp<br>and more...<p>Music Equalizer works with streaming music like Pandora, Spotify, etc.<p>Stock presets:<br>* Flat<br>* Classical<br>* Dance<br>* Folk<br>* Heavy Metal<br>* Hip Hop<br>* Jazz<br>* Normal<br>* Pop<br>* Rock <p>Also, you can remove all ads buying a key!<p>The best music equalizer on the Google Play!', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=br.com.rodrigokolb.musicequalizer', 'https://lh4.ggpht.com/vESZDAHp_uzqP6rFvbHLVeK1Gp4636nFiAdGZBVYa_aGbV3Fnk5YcRLNLB4qbf9h4g', 4.39, 'MUSIC_AND_AUDIO', 'Free', '500,000+', 'android.permission.RECORD_AUDIO, android.permission.MODIFY_AUDIO_SETTINGS, android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED, com.android.vending.BILLING'),
(662, 'com.google.android.setupwarlock', 'Nexus Q', 'Google Inc.', 'The Nexus Q app runs on any phone or tablet running Android system version 2.3.3 or later. You can use it with current versions of Google Play and YouTube apps to stream music, TV shows, videos, and HD movies to Nexus Q devices that are set up in your home.<p>After you install and open the Nexus Q app, the Google Play and YouTube apps on your phone or tablet will offer a new feature to stream entertainment through Nexus Q.<p>Each Nexus Q device is designed to control the equipment in one room: speakers, AV systems, TVs, and more. Each room with a Nexus Q appears in the Nexus Q app, where you can control what&#39;s playing and at what volume, or (for music only) stream to multiple rooms at the same time.<p>And when friends come to visit, they can also use the Nexus Q app to stream any of their own music or movies from Google Play through your Nexus Qs, using their own Android phones or tablets.<p>So you don&#39;t need a Nexus Q device to use the Nexus Q app. You just need a friend who has at least one Nexus Q and will let you stream your own music, movies, and TV shows through it.', 'https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.google.android.setupwarlock', 'http://lh5.ggpht.com/I8wnM8lVHKvKStS1iPOTnRQN9Yzjy9dBNOWyr657i1b4A4ya_VMB5R-G3By1xVRLZsrF', 4.17, 'MUSIC_AND_AUDIO', 'Free', '100,000+', 'android.permission.BLUETOOTH, android.permission.BLUETOOTH_ADMIN, android.permission.CHANGE_WIFI_MULTICAST_STATE, android.permission.CHANGE_WIFI_STATE, android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED, android.permission.BROADCAST_STICKY, android.permission.AUTHENTICATE_ACCOUNTS, android.permission.GET_ACCOUNTS, android.permission.MANAGE_ACCOUNTS, android.permission.USE_CREDENTIALS, com.google.android.providers.gsf.permission.READ_GSERVICES, com.google.android.providers.gsf.permission.WRITE_GSERVICES, android.permission.READ_SYNC_SETTINGS, android.permission.WRITE_SYNC_SETTINGS, android.permission.READ_SYNC_STATS